        "last_activity_date": 1516977066,
        "creation_date": 1516976914,
        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Converting a collection of subtype to collection of supertype",
        "body": "<p>What's the best way in Java  to convert a collection of a subtype to a collection of a supertype ?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>class A {}\nclass B extends A {}\n\nfinal A a = new B(); // OK.\n\nfinal Collection&lt;B&gt; bs = Arrays.asList(new B());\nfinal Collection&lt;A&gt; as1 = bs; // &lt;- Error\nfinal Collection&lt;A&gt; as2 = (Collection&lt;A&gt;) (Collection&lt;?&gt;) bs; // &lt;- Unchecked cast warning\nfinal Collection&lt;A&gt; as3 = bs.stream().collect(Collectors.toList()); // Browses through all the elements :-/\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I have to implement a method (defined in an interface) that returns a <code>Collection&lt;A&gt;<\/code> while the concrete result I get is a <code>Collection&lt;B&gt;<\/code> .<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 48463351,
